items.sentence: Mary met the man of her dreams just before her thirtieth birthday.
My father is going to prepare some delicious food for me tomorrow.
My grandfather has an antique television that he wants to give me.
The cat was pretty goofy and its energy never let up for a moment.
If your rent comes in past the fifth, a late charge will be added.
There's a chance that the rain will turn to snow during the night.
I wonder if Tom has ever asked Mary why she dropped out of school.
I wonder how many people born in the 19th century are still alive.
I'm glad that they fixed the heating system, but now it's too hot.
I'm going to be singing a cappella at a friend's wedding ceremony.
